type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative from Widdrington (Northumb), recorded as  <i>Vuderintuna</i>, about 1160."],"variants":[{"name":"Wethington","meanings":["English: habitational name, a shortened form of   Wetherington  ."]},{"name":"Wetherington","meanings":["English (Northumberland and Durham): from Widdrington (Northumberland). The placename derives from an Old English personal name <i>Widuhere</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."]},{"name":"Weatherington","meanings":["English (Northamptonshire): variant of   Wetherington  ."]},{"name":"Witherington","meanings":["English: either a variant of   Wetherington  , or perhaps a habitational name from Witherenden in Ticehurst (Sussex), Witherden Farm in Headcorn (Kent), or a lost place called <i>Witherington</i> or similar. The Sussex and Kent placenames probably derive from an Old English personal name <i>Wither</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>denn</i> ‘woodland pasture’."]}]},{"name":"Christiana","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval learned feminine form of   Christian .  As a recent revival it represents an elaborated form of   Christina .  It is also sometimes spelled  <b>Christianna</b> , under the influence of the name   Anna ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Christiana de Widdrington was born in 1336, in Widdrington, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, her father, Roger de Widdrington, was 31 and her mother, Elizabeth Acton, was 12. She married Sir Bertram de Monbourcher of Horton Castle in February 1358. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1387, in Horton, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 51."},"et":{"1336–1387":"1336–1387","1343–1426":"1343–1426","–1369":"–1369","1337–1388":"1337–1388",